r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When you see the confirmation message that the installation is complete, click&nbsp;<strong>Finish</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to800\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Finish\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_0/proc_par/step/step_par/img_0.img.png/Finish.png\" alt=\"Click Finish\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase header section\"><a name=\"main-pars_header_3\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"header\">\r\n<h2 id=\"id_43756\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Chrome: Download and install Acrobat Reader DC</span></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"main-pars_text_4\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Follow these steps to install Acrobat Reader DC using Google Chrome.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section procedure\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"proc_par proc_parsys\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Close all versions of Reader. Close any browser that is displaying a PDF.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Go to the <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://get.adobe.com/reader/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Adobe Acrobat Reader download</a> page and click <strong>Install now</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step/step_par/image_1001882723.img.jpg/win10.jpg\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">You need Windows 7 or later to run Acrobat Reader DC. If you&rsquo;re running an older version of Windows, the Adobe Reader download page looks like this:</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step/step_par/image.img.png/reader_alt_download_page_windows.png\" alt=\"Acrobat Reader download page for older versions\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_84124024\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><em>You can install an older version of Acrobat Reader. For instructions, see <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/content/help/en/acrobat/kb/install-reader-x-windows.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Install an older version of Adobe Reader | Windows</a>.</em></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Click <strong>Save</strong> to download the Reader installer.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When the downloaded file appears at the bottom of the browser window, click the .exe file for Reader.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"small\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click the Reader.exe file at the bottom of the browser\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step_3/step_par/image.img.png/file_saved.png\" alt=\"Click the Reader.exe file at the bottom of the browser\" /></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"note parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"help-note\">\r\n<p><span class=\"help-note-title\" style=\"color: #000000;\">Note:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Acrobat Reader DC installation is a two-part process: The installer is downloaded, and then Reader is installed. Be sure to wait until both parts are complete. A progress bar displays the time remaining.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"step section\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div class=\"step_par step_parsys\">\r\n<div class=\"parbase section text\"><a name=\"step_par_text_0\"></a>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div class=\"text\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When you see the confirmation message that the installation is complete, click&nbsp;<strong>Finish</strong>.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"image parbase section\">\r\n<div class=\"to800\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img class=\"cq-dd-image\" style=\"width: 100%;\" title=\"Click Finish\" src=\"https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/kb/install-reader-dc-windows/_jcr_content/main-pars/procedure_2/proc_par/step_5/step_par/img_0.img.png/Finish.png\" alt=\"Click Finish\" /></span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','2017-06-05 02:04:32','2017-08-02 05:51:47'),(24,1,1,'How to fix common issues after an AC upgrade?','2018-06-19','<ul>\r\n<li>AC Crashing</li>\r\n<li>Courselist Not Loading</li>\r\n<li>Audio/Video Device not Detected</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">The things that you can do when you encounter this issues are:</span></em></p>\r\n<p>A. Clean installation of the latest AC version.</p>\r\n<p>B. Clear your AC cache</p>\r\n<p>C. Conduct device checking</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em>Follow these instructions on how to:</em></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>A. Clean installation of the latest AC version</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>*Uninstall all previous AC version</em><br />1. Go to Control Panel and click on programs (via Start&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/shares/start.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"45\" height=\"33\" />&nbsp;or Windows search bar)</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/shares/Programs.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"183\" height=\"69\" /></p>\r\n<p>2. Select 51Talk AC then click Uninstall/Change</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/shares/ProgramFiles.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"635\" height=\"360\" /></p>\r\n<p>3.On the 51Talk AC Uninstaller window, click on <strong>&ldquo;Proceed Uninstall&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/photos/9/Uninstaller.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"615\" height=\"454\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>4.Wait for the uninstallation process to finish.</p>\r\n<p>5.Once uninstallation is complete, you may now start re-installing AC.</p>\r\n<p>6.For the latest version of AC, you may download the latest AC thru your mypage by clicking on this icon:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/shares/Icon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"86\" height=\"83\" /></p>\r\n<p>OR</p>\r\n<p>click on this link: <a href=\"https://ac.51talk.com/PcAc/version/51Talk-AC.2.14.0.54.exe\">https://ac.51talk.com/PcAc/version/51Talk-AC.2.14.0.55.exe</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>B.&nbsp;Clear AC Cache</strong></p>\r\n<p>Clearing AC cache can fix the lesson list or material load failed or display error issue</p>\r\n<p>1.On your AC main window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/menu.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"93\" height=\"40\" /></p>\r\n<p>2.Click on&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/system setting.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"127\" height=\"37\" /></p>\r\n<p>3.Click on <strong>Clean Button</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/photos/9/clean.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"375\" height=\"324\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>4.Then click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/yes button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"127\" height=\"36\" /></p>\r\n<p>5.AC will now initialize reboot to take effect</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/complete.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"144\" height=\"62\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>C.&nbsp;Setup Audio and Video Devices</strong></p>\r\n<p>After AC upgrade always redo the test to ensure default devices (Audio / Video) will be selected as default</p>\r\n<p>1.On the <strong>Device Checking </strong>window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/start_detect.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"110\" height=\"38\" /></p>\r\n<p>2.Selecting audio devices &gt; Click on yes if you can hear the instruction guide through your headset as default</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/testSpeaker.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"230\" height=\"220\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>**Otherwise click NO button and AC will select other Audio device as default.</p>\r\n<p>3.Selecting Microphone &gt; Please try to speak once initiated and an audio bar will be visible if microphone is working, then click yes</p>\r\n<p>4.Otherwise click &ldquo;Dissatisfied&rdquo; button and AC will select other Mic device as default.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/testMic.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"250\" /></p>\r\n<p>5.Selecting video camera &gt; AC will automatically look for Camera devices as default, if ever we wanted to change camera device just click &ldquo;Dissatisfied&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/TestCamera.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"237\" height=\"313\" /></p>','2018-05-18 01:40:41','2018-06-26 01:02:33'),(25,1,1,'What to do when lesson material is not loading','2018-06-19','<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3 Steps that you can do in resolving this isssue</p>\r\n<p><strong>A. Refresh your AC</strong></p>\r\n<p>- On your AC main window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/refresh.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"83\" height=\"32\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>B. Use backup classroom</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>-&nbsp;</strong>On your AC main window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/backupClassroom.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"148\" height=\"33\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/getLesson.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"361\" height=\"225\" /></p>\r\n<p><em>*Take note that your lesson will only show on your backup classroom within 1 hour of your current time.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>C. Clear your AC\'s cache</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><em>*It can fix any lesson material loading failed or display error issue</em></span></p>\r\n<p>1.On your AC main window, click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/menu.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"84\" height=\"36\" /></p>\r\n<p>2.Click on&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/system setting.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"113\" height=\"33\" /></p>\r\n<p>3.Click on <strong>Clean Button</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/photos/9/clean.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"396\" height=\"342\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>4.Then click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/yes button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"124\" height=\"35\" /></p>\r\n<p>5.AC will now initialize reboot to take effect</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/9/complete.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"170\" height=\"73\" /></p>','2018-05-18 01:49:11','2018-06-26 01:10:13'),(26,8,0,'Penalty Removal FAQs','2018-05-21','<p>Here are what you need to know in filing a dispute:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>How do I file a dispute?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you are marked as absent due to an AC or MyPage issue, contact Technical Support for dispute validation via <a href=\"http://phsupport.51talk.com/\">http://phsupport.51talk.com/</a></li>\r\n<li>Other absence should be filed to our Fees team by submitting a ticket via <a href=\"http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket\">http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li><strong>How will I know the result of the Tech Dispute Validation?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tech Dispute Validation will be sent via email within 24hours upon filing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li><strong>When will the penalty reversal reflect on my Lesson Fee Summary?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the Tech Dispute Validation results states that the penalty will be reversed within the current cut-off, it will reflect on your Lesson Fee Summary before the current cut-off ends.</li>\r\n<li>If the Tech Dispute Validation results states that the penalty is for supplementation on the next cutoff, the penalty will be supplemented and reflected on your Lesson Fee Summary before the next cut-off ends.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>** Take note that after tech validation, it will still undergo approval process. For follow ups on your penalty reversal/supplementation, you may submit a ticket via <a href=\"http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket\">http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket</a></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n<li><strong>What will happen to my penalty if there is an AC or MyPage outage?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If there is a system known issue (as posted on PH Support portal home page), your absence and/or penalty on the affected lesson will be reviewed for reversal. Once approved, it will automatically reflect on your Lesson Fee Summary.</li>\r\n<li>All system issues will NOT require tech validation, for concerns/follow-up, you may submit a ticket to our fees team via <a href=\"http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket\">http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n<li><strong>Why is my dispute invalid?</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All lessons filed under Dispute Validation undergo thorough checking. The result is determined by checking our system on any error or issues occurred within the lesson time affected.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>** Take note that all lessons are recorded on the system which allows your dispute validation team to further check on the main issue.</em></p>','2018-05-21 02:34:10','2018-05-29 23:32:06'),(27,8,0,'Penalty Removal: Steps on how to file','2018-05-23','<p>Issues that needs tech dispute validation</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Blank courselist &ndash; <a href=\"/descknow/1/1/25\"><em>click here for troubleshooting</em></a></li>\r\n<li>Lesson Material not loading &ndash; <a href=\"/descknow/1/1/25\"><em>click here for troubleshooting</em></a></li>\r\n<li>Audio/Video issues &ndash; <a href=\"/descknow/1/1/1\"><em>click here for troubleshooting</em></a></li>\r\n<li>Unfilled lesson memo absence due to AC/MyPage issue<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Filing a dispute validation:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Go to 51Talk support portal via <a href=\"http://phsupport.51talk.com/\">http://phsupport.51talk.com/</a></li>\r\n<li>Click tech support bubble<br /><img src=\"/photos/9/TechBubble.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"301\" height=\"117\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click on the specific issue for the troubleshooting steps on the issue you encountered.<br />- Make sure that you conduct the troubleshooting steps to avoid any future penalties.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n<li>Submit a ticket to tech support validation team</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/9/submit ticket.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"39\" /></li>\r\n<li>Make sure to include the following details<br />a. Lesson Date and Time<br />b. AC Version<br />c. Issue encountered<br />d. Screenshot of the error</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n<li>Wait for the result within 24 hours after filing.</li>\r\n<li>Result will be sent via email.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>**Other absence penalty should be file to our Fees team by submitting a ticket via <a href=\"http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket\">http://support.51talk.com/submit_ticket</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2018-05-22 23:30:41','2018-05-22 23:36:40'),(28,1,1,'All You Need to Know about AC 2.14.0.55','2018-06-19','<p><strong>All you need to know on AC 2.14.0.55 Windows platform</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Personalized Feature</li>\r\n<li>Enlarged Video Format</li>\r\n<li>Automatic AC error detection</li>\r\n<li>Automatic CPU and Ram usage detection</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Personalized Feature</strong></p>\r\n<p>A New feature of AC that enhance your video AC experienced to be more fun and creative by adding Video background on Both Student Teacher with lots of Face mask and Stickers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s how to activate:</p>\r\n<p>Click on the Personalized button located besides the star sending feature&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/personalized.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"381\" height=\"36\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Lots of Fun feature to choose from all you have to do is drag and drop the selected stickers or Face Mask to your video screen and student</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/stickers.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"275\" height=\"113\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/stickers and mask.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"331\" height=\"208\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>FAQ on Personalized feature</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: How can I remove the sticker that I placed on Video Screen and student?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Click on the Broom Icon located on your video screen to remove the stickers or any features added.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: Can my student add their own or removed the personalized fun features?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Teacher are the ones that can activate or deactivate the feature.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: Is the Personalized Feature only available on kid&rsquo;s lesson?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Yes</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Enlarged Video Format</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Simply enlarged your video screen to better be seen by students</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s How to activate:</p>\r\n<p>Click on the &ldquo;enlarged video button&rdquo; located below your video screen</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/enlarge icon.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"194\" height=\"162\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/enlarge.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"499\" height=\"261\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>FAQ on Enlarged Video format</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: How am I Going to revert back the enlarge video screen?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Click on the &ldquo;Restore&rdquo; button and it will revert back to its original state</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: Do Student have this feature?</p>\r\n<p>Answer: It is only applicable on the teacher side</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Automatic AC detection is the new AC intellisense</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>AC can now detect the error automatic and will notify the user CPU / RAM usage / Network / Devices and provide a possible fix.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/auto ac.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"658\" height=\"325\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;The user will be notified if the CPU and Ram usage are on critical level which is cause by to many windows applications opened.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/photos/8/AC 2.14.0.55 feature/cpu ram detect.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"721\" height=\"346\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>FAQ Functionality </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: I notice that the Lesson timer doesn&rsquo;t turn red as an indicator that lesson is near end</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Developer had been informed and it&rsquo;s under development</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Question: Praisal sound is not visible anymore</p>\r\n<p>Answer: It has been removed as part of AC optimization</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Questions: &nbsp;I already installed the AC 2.14.0.55 and I cannot find the personalized feature on any of my kid&rsquo;s lesson.</p>\r\n<p>Answer: Personalized is currently activated on teacher under HBT-FT</p>','2018-06-12 21:51:34','2018-06-26 00:53:34'),(29,8,0,'How to file a penalty dispute ticket','2018-06-19','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please prepare the following:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Lesson Date and time affected</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 6/01/2018&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 19:00 &ndash; 19:30</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li>Concern type : AC No scheduled</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li>Screenshot as a proof</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>How to file a request:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Click on the Send us ticket located on this article and follow the steps on the image below</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"/photos/8/Penalty removal/submi ticket.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1257\" height=\"612\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2018-06-19 04:31:11','2018-06-26 01:11:23'),(30,8,0,'Outage: AC No Schedule / Blank Courselist FIXED','2018-06-19','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>AC Course List issues Fixed! , all penalties with regards to this issue wil be reversed. No need to submit fees disputes for reversal</h4>\r\n<h4><strong>Other Info:</strong> Start time: 20:05 End time: 21:29</h4>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','2018-06-21 04:50:48','2018-06-21 05:37:34');
